        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 3:57PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 357 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ellicott, or 22 miles east of Colorado Springs, moving south at 5
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ellicott.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
